Breast-Like Comfort and Prevent Drool Rash - Our baby soothie pacifier allows your child to self-soothe by exercising their instinctive sucking instinct in the most natural way possible, by mimicking both the shape and soft materials of mothers’ breast. In addition, our two larger ventilation holes allow air to flow to prevent drool rash.

This one-piece construction makes cleaning and sterilizing easier with no chance of water pooling in the nipple. Moonkie's dust-free technology makes silicone surface less sticky, which won’t attract dust and hair.

Stylish Pacifier and Ideal Gift for Baby Shower-With scalloped edges that mimic flower petals, the Moonkie Daisy pacifier takes the thoughtful design of our classic pacifier and adds in a whimsical, charming design. Moonkie newborn pacifiers provide you with a wide variety of earthy tones. You can perfect match your baby's various styles of clothing and pacifier clip. In addition, our pacifiers with exquisite packaging is a perfect gift for baby shower.

Safety First and Ultra-Durable-At Moonkie, safety is EVERYTHING! Our pacifiers exceed CPSIA standard and also comply with the stricter European standard (EN1400-A2:2018) for safety and comfort requirements. Ultra-durable and unbreakable silicone is the ideal material for pacifier – no more cracked plastic shield or spending money to replace them! Suitable for 6 months + , with no parts to break off and zero choking hazard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Happy mama, happy baby
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these and Frigg pacifiers at the same time to try. These are easier to clean and don’t get water trapped inside, the nipple is softer and more easily accepted by my EBF baby, and nearly half the cost. I thought they would be too heavy because they’re fully silicone and not partly made of plastic but they’re actually still very lightweight. My baby doesn’t love pacifiers in general but we’re trying out different brands and shapes and she actually took this one for a bit which is saying something. She will gag on other bulb pacifiers because they’re too long but these are appropriately sized for smaller babies. I honestly don’t even think I would have noticed the seam if others hadn’t mentioned it here. There is only one other pacifier she took as easily as this one (Tommee Tippee Ultralight) but it didn’t have a spot for a pacifier clip and didn’t come in cute colors. I hope she ends up liking these because they’re so cute and have the features I’m looking for!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I recently learned that most pacifier brands market themselves as “100% natural rubber” but are made of latex, which can be harmful to your little ones since they can develop a latex allergy due to constant exposure to latex! So I’m so thankful I found some 100% silicon pacifiers! My daughter took to them so quickly & they are so beyond easy to clean

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Comparable to expensive competitors
reviews.reviewText: Baby took to it right away!I have a 5 month old foster baby who has had issues with maintaining a latch on a bottle or pacifier. I was able to get her to take the rubber bulb shaped pacifiers but they degrade quickly and are much more expensive than these silicone ones. I had been trying to find one that's similar to those but all silicone which this one is. I also LOVE that the shield faces away from the baby's face which supports healthy skin and keeps their airway clear. She seems to be able to hold this one better and it's cute with the flower shape. The nipple isn't as smooth as most silicone pacifiers which for her is great as I think thats why she prefers the rubber ones - they're more skin like.I took off one star because the handle doesn't pivot to lay flat, which I do like that about the rubber ones as baby likes to snuggle her face into me, or the crib. I also wonder about the slight space between the nipple and the shield and if that's going to get gross. I put her binkys in the dishwasher daily. Will update later if that becomes a further issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than bibs
reviews.reviewText: I have a picky, tongue tied, exclusively BF baby... bibs is all she has been willing to take so far, but they are expensive so I thought we'd give these a try. This product has the same shape and feel as bibs, but easier to keep clean! No hidden crevices for mold to grow in is a HUGE plus. My only complaint is that the nipple has a more prominent seam where the mold comes together. I was worried that would be a deal breaker for my picky baby but she doesn't seem to mind. She takes it just the same as the bibs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cute but questionable durability
reviews.reviewText: I decided to give these pacis a try. My daughter is almost 2 and still loves her paci, but obviously she has teeth and sometimes chews on it. She was being pretty aggressive and managed to rip the nipple completely in half. At this point we’d only had them a couple weeks and because I bought 4, they weren’t weakened from a lot of use as she was switching between them. I think we’ll stick to our tried and true Tommee Tippees from now on. Much thicker, sturdier silicone. Two kids worth of pacis and not a one has ever ripped like that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My baby loves these pacifiers. She had only ever taken a bulb shaped pacifier and these are 10/10 and significantly cheaper than other brands. I like that the bulb part is not enclosed on the back giving me peace of mind that no bacteria or moisture is getting trapped. Have bought multiple already

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to clean
reviews.reviewText: I am pleasantly surprised how much I like these. I was buying a much more expensive well known brand - and tried these to see if I could save 8-10$. I like how the nipple in the binkie is open, so water does not get inside and make it all cloudy and unsanitary. I love the feel of them. Very soft. Colors are so cute too.So far so good!! I do agree that I wish more came in a pack but this seems to be across the board to only supply two in a pack lately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just do it
reviews.reviewText: These are absolutely wonderful. They’re soft and bendable so if my daughter spits it out at night and lays on top, she’s still comfortable. LOVE that they’re dishwasher safe too!
